Class NumberConverterToVectorAdapter<InputType>

  • java.lang.Object

  • Type Parameters:
    InputType - The input type to convert encode into a number, which is then adapted to be used in a Vector.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataConverter<InputType,Vector>, DataToVectorEncoder<InputType>, Evaluator<InputType,Vector>, VectorFactoryContainer, VectorOutputEvaluator<InputType,Vector>, CloneableSerializable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class NumberConverterToVectorAdapter<InputType>
extends AbstractToVectorEncoder<InputType>
